@postsuffering @samswoora @moreisdifferent If so, interesting - especially if his nociception was functional ("Pain is just a useful signaling mechanism", say a few lucky outliers) Males tend to engage in more rough-and-tumble behavior. 
Could the problem of pain be genetically fixed this century?
 https://t.co/hvtL7Wivku

@davidshaw26 @GreenComrade @BurntOutUtopian @Unpop_Science Nature has thrown up a species capable of editing its own source code and fixing the problem of suffering throughout the living world. 
Critics say compassionate stewardship of Nature would be "unnatural". 
But the same could be said of wearing clothes...

@samswoora @moreisdifferent Most EAs are classical utilitarians. But classical utilitarianism has monstrous implications. Imagine a genie offers me super-exponential growth of my happiness at the expense of an exponential growth of your suffering. 
As a NU, I decline. 
The classical utilitarian must accept.

@GreenComrade @davidshaw26 @BurntOutUtopian @Unpop_Science Pain &amp; happiness don’t radically differ across animal species - any more than across races. Their neurological &amp; genetic pathways are strongly conserved. 
Ants? 
Soon every millimetre of the biosphere will be computationally accessible to surveillance, micromanagement &amp; control…

@GreenComrade @davidshaw26 @BurntOutUtopian @Unpop_Science Digital zombies are idiots savants. 
But AI can help us reprogram the biosphere, end Nature's snuff movie, civilise the living world and create life based entirely on gradients of bliss. 
An approximation of health as defined by the WHO should be the birthright of all sentience.

@SunnyBe4r @heyorson @FelixDelong “If you think this Universe is bad, you should see some of the others.”
(Philip K. Dick)
Yes. Any aesthetic or intellectual satisfaction one may derive from the elegance of a zero ontology / Everett as an explanation-space is extinguished if one thinks through the implications.

@gniksAtsuJmi @BugRib Yes. If non-materialist physicalism is true, mathematical physics describes patterns of qualia. The solutions to the equations of QFT encode the textures of experience. Animal minds are special - but not ontologically special. 
Crazy stuff.
https://t.co/7OUSUk01U2

@LJumbotron @algekalipso “Homo sapiens, the first truly free species, is about to decommission natural selection, the force that made us. Soon we must look deep within ourselves &amp; decide what we wish to become.” (E.O. Wilson)
Selection pressure is poised to intensify, not diminish.
Farewell to suffering.

@lucas65537 @algekalipso A nice analysis. Classical Turing machines are zombies. They don’t have minds. They can’t wake up. They aren’t nascent AGI. They can’t replace sentience. The ignorance of classical computers is architecturally hardwired. 
But I love ChatGPT:
https://t.co/gboHXMr5Og

@drimmi1zz2 @algekalipso @NathanpmYoung "Life preys upon life. This is biology's most fundamental fact”
