OK, it's a continuum. 
But we should be cautious about wanting all the creature comforts of life for ourselves and denying them to others.

@JoshuaHiles @StijnBruers @Rob_Chipman @herbivorize @Nikolaj_Bi @AdamHartScience @PaulDolman3 @WilliamsMitche @SteveCJjones @StephenCorrySvl @Alexander_Lees @AmiesPhilip @KSAfricaHack @Survival @webmaster Protecting vulnerable human and nonhuman animals is best done by consensus. Are there circumstances where we should prioritise the interests of the victims? 
Yes - IMO. 
There is no "right to harm".

